categories.name: Adpositional Expression (Strong)
categories.description: Adposition (preposition/postposition) or case marker: single-word or strong multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Adposition (preposition/postposition) or case marker: single-word or strong multiword expression

categories.name: Verbal Expression (Strong)
categories.description: Verb: single-word or strong multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Verb: single-word or strong multiword expression

categories.name: Nominal Expression (Strong)
categories.description: Noun: single-word or strong multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Noun: single-word or strong multiword expression

categories.name: Other strong expression
categories.description: Other expression (single-word or strong multiword)
categories.tooltip: Other strong expression

categories.name: Verbal Expression (Weak)
categories.description: Verb: weak multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Verb: weak multiword expression

categories.name: Adpostitional Expression (Weak)
categories.description: Adposition (preposition/postposition) or case marker: weak multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Adposition (preposition/postposition) or case marker: weak multiword expression

categories.name: Other Weak MWE
categories.description: Other Weak Multiword Expression (not nominal, verbal, or prepositional)
categories.tooltip: Other Weak MWE (not nominal, verbal, or prepositional)

categories.name: Nominal Expression (Weak)
categories.description: Noun: weak multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Noun: weak multiword expression

categories.description: Unclear/unsure
categories.tooltip: Unclear/unsure

categories.description: Unintelligible or violently ungrammatical
categories.tooltip: Unintelligible or violently ungrammatical

categories.name: Temporal
categories.description:
Abstract supercategory for temporal descriptions: when, for
how long, how often, how many times, etc. something happened
or will happen.
categories.tooltip: Abstract supercategory for temporal descriptions

categories.name: StartTime
categories.description: When the event denoted by the governor begins.
categories.tooltip: When the event denoted by the governor begins

categories.name: EndTime
categories.description: When the event denoted by the governor finishes.
categories.tooltip: When the event denoted by the governor finishes

categories.name: Frequency
categories.description:
At what rate something happens or continues, or the instance
of repetition that the event represents.
categories.tooltip: At what rate something happens or continues, or the instance of repetition that the event represents

categories.name: Time
categories.description:
When something happened or will happen, in relation to an
explicit or implicit reference time or event.
categories.tooltip: When something happened or will happen

categories.name: Duration
categories.description:
Indication of how long an event or state lasts (with reference to
an amount of time or time period/larger event that it spans).
categories.tooltip: Indication of how long an event or state lasts

categories.name: Interval
categories.description:
A marker that points retrospectively or prospectively in time,
and if transitive, marks the time elapsed between two points in
time.
categories.tooltip: A marker that points retrospectively or prospectively in time

categories.name: Source
categories.description: Initial location, condition, or value. May be abstract.
categories.tooltip: Initial location, condition, or value. May be abstract.

categories.name: Goal
categories.description: Final location (destination), condition, or value. May be abstract.
categories.tooltip: Final location (destination), condition, or value. May be abstract.

categories.name: Direction
categories.description: How motion or an object is aimed/oriented.
categories.tooltip: How motion or an object is aimed/oriented

categories.name: Extent
categories.description: The size of a path.
categories.tooltip: The size of a path

categories.name: Manner
categories.description: Description of how something happens or exists that does not directly invoke a location, path, or temporal or causal relation. Often the "style" of something.
categories.tooltip: Description of how something happens or exists

categories.name: Purpose
categories.description:
Something that somebody wants to bring about, asserted to be
why something was done, is the case, or exists.
categories.tooltip: Something that somebody wants to bring about, asserted to be why something was done, is the case, or exists

categories.name: Causer
categories.description: Instigator of, and a core participant in, an event.
categories.tooltip: Instigator of, and a core participant in, an event

categories.name: Agent
categories.description: Animate instigator of an action (typically volitional).
categories.tooltip: Animate instigator of an action (typically volitional)

categories.name: Co-Agent
categories.description: Second semantically core participant that would otherwise be labeled Agent, but which is adpositionally marked in contrast with an Agent occupying a non-oblique syntactic position (subject or object). Typically, the Agent and Co-Agent engage in the event in a reciprocal fashion.
categories.tooltip: Second semantically core participant

categories.name: Theme
categories.description: Undergoer that is a semantically core participant in an event or state, and that does not meet the criteria for any other label.
categories.tooltip: Undergoer that is a semantically core participant

categories.name: Co-Theme
categories.description: Second semantically core undergoer that would otherwise be labeled Theme, but which is adpositionally marked in contrast with a Theme occupying a non-oblique syntactic position (subject or object).
categories.tooltip: Second semantically core undergoer

categories.name: Topic
categories.description: Information content or subject matter in communication or cognition.
categories.tooltip: Information content or subject matter in communication or cognition

categories.name: Stimulus
categories.description: That which is perceived or experienced (bodily, perceptually, or emotionally).
categories.tooltip: That which is perceived or experienced (bodily, perceptually, or emotionally)

categories.name: Experiencer
categories.description: Animate who is aware of a bodily experience, perception, emotion, or mental state.
categories.tooltip: Animate who is aware of a bodily experience, perception, emotion, or mental state

categories.name: Explanation
categories.description: Assertion of why something happens or is the case.
categories.tooltip: Assertion of why something happens or is the case

categories.name: Originator
categories.description: Animate who is the initial possessor or creator/producer of something, including the speaker/communicator of information. Excludes events where transfer/communication is not framed as unidirectional.
categories.tooltip: Animate who is the initial possessor or creator/producer of something

categories.name: Recipient
categories.description: Animate who is the (actual or intended) final possessor of a thing or message. Excludes events where transfer/communication is not framed as unidirectional.
categories.tooltip: Animate who is the (actual or intended) final possessor of a thing or message

categories.name: Cost
categories.description: An amount (typically of money) that is linked to an item or service that it pays for/could pay for, or given as the amount earned or owed.
categories.tooltip: An amount (typically of money) that is linked to an item or service that it pays for/could pay for

categories.name: Beneficiary
categories.description: Animate or personified undergoer that is (potentially) advantaged or disadvantaged by the event or state.
categories.tooltip: Animate or personified undergoer that is (potentially) advantaged or disadvantaged by the event or state

categories.name: Instrument
categories.description:
An entity that facilitates an action by applying intermediate
causal force.
categories.tooltip: An entity that facilitates an action by applying intermediate causal force

categories.name: Configuration
categories.description: Thing, usually an entity or property, that is involved in a static relationship to some other entity.
categories.tooltip: Thing, usually an entity or property, that is involved in a static relationship to some other entity

categories.name: Identity
categories.description: A category being ascribed to something, or something belonging to the category denoted by the governor.
categories.tooltip: A category being ascribed to something, or something belonging to the category denoted by the governor

categories.name: Species
categories.description: A category qualified by sort, type, kind, species, breed, etc. Includes variety, selection, range, assortment, etc. meaning ‘many different kinds’.
categories.tooltip: A category qualified by sort, type, kind, species, breed, etc.

categories.name: Gestalt
categories.description: Generalized notion of “whole” understood with reference to a component part, possession, set member, or characteristic. See Characteristic.
categories.tooltip: Generalized notion of “whole”

categories.name: Whole
categories.description: Something described with respect to its part, portion, subevent, subset, or set element. See Part/Portion.
categories.tooltip: Something described with respect to its part, portion, subevent, subset, or set element

categories.name: Characteristic
categories.description: Generalized notion of a part, feature, possession, or the contents or composition of something, understood with respect to that thing (the Gestalt).
categories.tooltip: Generalized notion of a part, feature, possession, or the contents or composition of something

categories.name: Possession
categories.description: That which some Possessor (animate or personified, e.g. an institution) has, and which is not part of their body or inherent to their identity/character but could, in principle, be taken away.
categories.tooltip: That which some Possessor (animate or personified, e.g. an institution) has

categories.name: Possessor
categories.description: Animate who has something (the Possession) which is not part of their body or inherent to their identity/character but could, in principle, be taken away.
categories.tooltip: Animate who has something (the Possession)

categories.name: Part/Portion
categories.description: A part, portion, subevent, subset, or set element (e.g., an example or exception) of some Whole.
categories.tooltip: A part, portion, subevent, subset, or set element (e.g., an example or exception) of some Whole

categories.name: Stuff
categories.description: The members comprising a group/ensemble, or the material comprising some unit of substance. Stuff is distinguished from other instances of Part/Portion in fully covering (or “summarizing”) the aggregate whole.
categories.tooltip: The members comprising a group/ensemble, or the material comprising some unit of substance

categories.name: Accompanier
categories.description: Entity that another entity is together with.
categories.tooltip: Entity that another entity is together with

categories.name: ComparisonRef
categories.description: The reference point in an explicit comparison (or contrast), i.e., an expression indicating that something is similar/analogous to, different from, or the same as something else.
categories.tooltip: The reference point in an explicit comparison (or contrast)

categories.name: Quantity
categories.description: Something measured by a quantity denoted by the governor.
categories.tooltip: Something measured by a quantity denoted by the governor

categories.name: Approximator
categories.description: An “operator” that semantically takes a measurement, quantity, or range as an argument and “transforms” it in some way into a new measurement, quantity, or range.
categories.tooltip: An “operator” that “transforms” a measurement, quantity, or range

categories.name: OrgRole
categories.description: Organization or institution with which an individual has a stable affiliation, such as membership or a business relationship.
categories.tooltip: Organization or institution with which an individual has a stable affiliation

categories.name: SocialRel
categories.description: Entity, such as an institution or another individual, with which an individual has a stable affiliation.
categories.tooltip: Entity, such as an institution or another individual, with which an individual has a stable affiliation

categories.name: RateUnit
categories.description: Unit of measure in a rate expression.
categories.tooltip: Unit of measure in a rate expression

categories.name: Circumstance
categories.description: Macrolabel for labels pertaining to space and time; abstract/metaphoric locations such as states; and other categories that usually constitute semantically non-core properties of events.
categories.tooltip: Macrolabel for labels pertaining to space and time

categories.name: InsteadOf
categories.description: A default or already established thing for which something else stands in or is chosen as an alternative.
categories.tooltip: A default or already established thing for which something else stands in or is chosen as an alternative

categories.name: Participant
categories.description: Thing, usually an entity, that plays a causal role in an event.
categories.tooltip: Thing, usually an entity, that plays a causal role in an event

categories.name: Path
categories.description: The ground that must be covered in order for the motion to be complete.
categories.tooltip: The ground that must be covered in order for the motion to be complete.

categories.name: Means
categories.description: Secondary action or event that characterizes how the main event happens or is achieved.
categories.tooltip: Secondary action or event that characterizes how the main event happens or is achieved.

categories.name: Locus
categories.description: Location, condition, or value. May be abstract.
categories.tooltip: Location, condition, or value. May be abstract.

categories.name: `r
categories.description: Adverbial expression that does not count as a preposition or PP. E.g., "too" and "then" when spelled correctly (as opposed to "to", "than").
categories.tooltip: Adverbial expression that does not count as a preposition or PP

categories.name: `o
categories.description: Indefinite pronoun (tagged as a noun in PTB). (For historical reasons most pronouns are labeled ` -- `o was only recently introduced.)
categories.tooltip: Indefinite pronoun

categories.name: `j
categories.description: Adjectival expression.
categories.tooltip: Adjectival expression

categories.name: `i
categories.description: The word "to" used as infinitive marker, but not marking a Purpose or Function adjunct. Includes complements ("want to").
categories.tooltip: The word "to" used as infinitive marker, but not marking a Purpose or Function adjunct

categories.name: `d
categories.description: Discourse expression. Excludes subordinators marking a semantic role (such as time or explanation). For historical reasons some discourse expressions are labeled `.
categories.tooltip: Discourse expression

categories.name: `a
categories.description: Auxiliaries not POS-tagged as MD. Includes multiword "quasi-modals" like "have to" indicating necessity or obligation.
categories.tooltip: Auxiliaries not POS-tagged as MD. Includes multiword "quasi-modals" like "have to" indicating necessity or obligation

categories.description: ​Used for miscellaneous words that do not deserve supersenses, including "as" in as-as constructions, emoticons, and some other cases that were annotated before the label refinements below (`d, `o, etc.) were introduced.
categories.tooltip: ​Used for miscellaneous words that do not deserve supersenses

passage.text:
They are like family .
With higher than average prices to boot !
That was 4 years ago .
Well , not much I can say except I 'm very disappointed with this experience .
Clean store , friendly check - out staff up front .
Gerry pleasantly said " since I am already here why do n't we give it shot .
it s like a pizza roll , but they just toss ham and cheese inside .
Do n't get the rooms off the two kitchens .
Right near Chelan .
STAY AWAY !!!
Fantastic food served without pretense , very reasonably priced wine selections .
I called over the weekend due to clogged kitchen sink .
I won a golf lesson certificate with Adz through a charity auction .
and there prices are really good !
Thank you Ana I hope to see you in the future under  better  circumstances .
Branch out and try something other than the Pad Thai , the curries are fantastic .
Because of the ants I dropped them to a 3 star .
I have  nothing but  fantastic  things  to say .
Sent scented flowers home instead of postcards .
First room had used tissues next to the bed and I requested it be rectified .
Fantastic for kids
Atmosphere is always fun , the assortment of customers adds entertainment to the meal
Cold , slimy , tasteless however is the same in all languages and foods .
They did a vehicle wrap for my Toyota Venza that looks amazing .
Right out of college I called the salon and explained my situation .
One of the worst experiences I 've ever had with a auto repair shop .
There were occasional bears on the deck in the morning .
Do n't think I 've ever been charged before .

parent.name: Multiword Expressions
parent.description: Strong MWEs (including single-word expressions) and weak MWEs
parent.tooltip: Strong MWEs (including single-word expressions) and weak MWEs

categories.name: Adpositional Expression (Strong)
categories.description: Adposition (preposition/postposition) or case marker: single-word or strong multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Adposition (preposition/postposition) or case marker: single-word or strong multiword expression

categories.name: Verbal Expression (Strong)
categories.description: Verb: single-word or strong multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Verb: single-word or strong multiword expression

categories.name: Nominal Expression (Strong)
categories.description: Noun: single-word or strong multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Noun: single-word or strong multiword expression

categories.name: Other strong expression
categories.description: Other expression (single-word or strong multiword)
categories.tooltip: Other strong expression

categories.name: Verbal Expression (Weak)
categories.description: Verb: weak multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Verb: weak multiword expression

categories.name: Adpostitional Expression (Weak)
categories.description: Adposition (preposition/postposition) or case marker: weak multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Adposition (preposition/postposition) or case marker: weak multiword expression

categories.name: Other Weak MWE
categories.description: Other Weak Multiword Expression (not nominal, verbal, or prepositional)
categories.tooltip: Other Weak MWE (not nominal, verbal, or prepositional)

categories.name: Nominal Expression (Weak)
categories.description: Noun: weak multiword expression
categories.tooltip: Noun: weak multiword expression

categories.description: Unclear/unsure
categories.tooltip: Unclear/unsure

categories.description: Unintelligible or violently ungrammatical
categories.tooltip: Unintelligible or violently ungrammatical

categories.name: Temporal
categories.description:
Abstract supercategory for temporal descriptions: when, for
how long, how often, how many times, etc. something happened
or will happen.
categories.tooltip: Abstract supercategory for temporal descriptions

categories.name: StartTime
categories.description: When the event denoted by the governor begins.
categories.tooltip: When the event denoted by the governor begins

categories.name: EndTime
categories.description: When the event denoted by the governor finishes.
categories.tooltip: When the event denoted by the governor finishes

categories.name: Frequency
categories.description:
At what rate something happens or continues, or the instance
of repetition that the event represents.
categories.tooltip: At what rate something happens or continues, or the instance of repetition that the event represents

categories.name: Time
categories.description:
When something happened or will happen, in relation to an
explicit or implicit reference time or event.
categories.tooltip: When something happened or will happen

categories.name: Duration
categories.description:
Indication of how long an event or state lasts (with reference to
an amount of time or time period/larger event that it spans).
categories.tooltip: Indication of how long an event or state lasts

categories.name: Interval
categories.description:
A marker that points retrospectively or prospectively in time,
and if transitive, marks the time elapsed between two points in
time.
categories.tooltip: A marker that points retrospectively or prospectively in time

categories.name: Source
categories.description: Initial location, condition, or value. May be abstract.
categories.tooltip: Initial location, condition, or value. May be abstract.

categories.name: Goal
categories.description: Final location (destination), condition, or value. May be abstract.
categories.tooltip: Final location (destination), condition, or value. May be abstract.

categories.name: Direction
categories.description: How motion or an object is aimed/oriented.
categories.tooltip: How motion or an object is aimed/oriented

categories.name: Extent
categories.description: The size of a path.
categories.tooltip: The size of a path

categories.name: Manner
categories.description: Description of how something happens or exists that does not directly invoke a location, path, or temporal or causal relation. Often the "style" of something.
categories.tooltip: Description of how something happens or exists

categories.name: Purpose
categories.description:
Something that somebody wants to bring about, asserted to be
why something was done, is the case, or exists.
categories.tooltip: Something that somebody wants to bring about, asserted to be why something was done, is the case, or exists

categories.name: Causer
categories.description: Instigator of, and a core participant in, an event.
categories.tooltip: Instigator of, and a core participant in, an event

categories.name: Agent
categories.description: Animate instigator of an action (typically volitional).
categories.tooltip: Animate instigator of an action (typically volitional)

categories.name: Co-Agent
categories.description: Second semantically core participant that would otherwise be labeled Agent, but which is adpositionally marked in contrast with an Agent occupying a non-oblique syntactic position (subject or object). Typically, the Agent and Co-Agent engage in the event in a reciprocal fashion.
categories.tooltip: Second semantically core participant

categories.name: Theme
categories.description: Undergoer that is a semantically core participant in an event or state, and that does not meet the criteria for any other label.
categories.tooltip: Undergoer that is a semantically core participant

categories.name: Co-Theme
categories.description: Second semantically core undergoer that would otherwise be labeled Theme, but which is adpositionally marked in contrast with a Theme occupying a non-oblique syntactic position (subject or object).
categories.tooltip: Second semantically core undergoer

categories.name: Topic
categories.description: Information content or subject matter in communication or cognition.
categories.tooltip: Information content or subject matter in communication or cognition

categories.name: Stimulus
categories.description: That which is perceived or experienced (bodily, perceptually, or emotionally).
categories.tooltip: That which is perceived or experienced (bodily, perceptually, or emotionally)

categories.name: Experiencer
categories.description: Animate who is aware of a bodily experience, perception, emotion, or mental state.
categories.tooltip: Animate who is aware of a bodily experience, perception, emotion, or mental state

categories.name: Explanation
categories.description: Assertion of why something happens or is the case.
categories.tooltip: Assertion of why something happens or is the case

categories.name: Originator
categories.description: Animate who is the initial possessor or creator/producer of something, including the speaker/communicator of information. Excludes events where transfer/communication is not framed as unidirectional.
categories.tooltip: Animate who is the initial possessor or creator/producer of something

categories.name: Recipient
categories.description: Animate who is the (actual or intended) final possessor of a thing or message. Excludes events where transfer/communication is not framed as unidirectional.
categories.tooltip: Animate who is the (actual or intended) final possessor of a thing or message

categories.name: Cost
categories.description: An amount (typically of money) that is linked to an item or service that it pays for/could pay for, or given as the amount earned or owed.
categories.tooltip: An amount (typically of money) that is linked to an item or service that it pays for/could pay for

categories.name: Beneficiary
categories.description: Animate or personified undergoer that is (potentially) advantaged or disadvantaged by the event or state.
categories.tooltip: Animate or personified undergoer that is (potentially) advantaged or disadvantaged by the event or state

categories.name: Instrument
categories.description:
An entity that facilitates an action by applying intermediate
causal force.
categories.tooltip: An entity that facilitates an action by applying intermediate causal force

categories.name: Configuration
categories.description: Thing, usually an entity or property, that is involved in a static relationship to some other entity.
categories.tooltip: Thing, usually an entity or property, that is involved in a static relationship to some other entity

categories.name: Identity
categories.description: A category being ascribed to something, or something belonging to the category denoted by the governor.
categories.tooltip: A category being ascribed to something, or something belonging to the category denoted by the governor

categories.name: Species
categories.description: A category qualified by sort, type, kind, species, breed, etc. Includes variety, selection, range, assortment, etc. meaning ‘many different kinds’.
categories.tooltip: A category qualified by sort, type, kind, species, breed, etc.

categories.name: Gestalt
categories.description: Generalized notion of “whole” understood with reference to a component part, possession, set member, or characteristic. See Characteristic.
categories.tooltip: Generalized notion of “whole”

categories.name: Whole
categories.description: Something described with respect to its part, portion, subevent, subset, or set element. See Part/Portion.
categories.tooltip: Something described with respect to its part, portion, subevent, subset, or set element

categories.name: Characteristic
categories.description: Generalized notion of a part, feature, possession, or the contents or composition of something, understood with respect to that thing (the Gestalt).
categories.tooltip: Generalized notion of a part, feature, possession, or the contents or composition of something

categories.name: Possession
categories.description: That which some Possessor (animate or personified, e.g. an institution) has, and which is not part of their body or inherent to their identity/character but could, in principle, be taken away.
categories.tooltip: That which some Possessor (animate or personified, e.g. an institution) has

categories.name: Possessor
categories.description: Animate who has something (the Possession) which is not part of their body or inherent to their identity/character but could, in principle, be taken away.
categories.tooltip: Animate who has something (the Possession)

categories.name: Part/Portion
categories.description: A part, portion, subevent, subset, or set element (e.g., an example or exception) of some Whole.
categories.tooltip: A part, portion, subevent, subset, or set element (e.g., an example or exception) of some Whole

categories.name: Stuff
categories.description: The members comprising a group/ensemble, or the material comprising some unit of substance. Stuff is distinguished from other instances of Part/Portion in fully covering (or “summarizing”) the aggregate whole.
categories.tooltip: The members comprising a group/ensemble, or the material comprising some unit of substance

categories.name: Accompanier
categories.description: Entity that another entity is together with.
categories.tooltip: Entity that another entity is together with

categories.name: ComparisonRef
categories.description: The reference point in an explicit comparison (or contrast), i.e., an expression indicating that something is similar/analogous to, different from, or the same as something else.
categories.tooltip: The reference point in an explicit comparison (or contrast)

categories.name: Quantity
categories.description: Something measured by a quantity denoted by the governor.
categories.tooltip: Something measured by a quantity denoted by the governor

categories.name: Approximator
categories.description: An “operator” that semantically takes a measurement, quantity, or range as an argument and “transforms” it in some way into a new measurement, quantity, or range.
categories.tooltip: An “operator” that “transforms” a measurement, quantity, or range

categories.name: OrgRole
categories.description: Organization or institution with which an individual has a stable affiliation, such as membership or a business relationship.
categories.tooltip: Organization or institution with which an individual has a stable affiliation

categories.name: SocialRel
categories.description: Entity, such as an institution or another individual, with which an individual has a stable affiliation.
categories.tooltip: Entity, such as an institution or another individual, with which an individual has a stable affiliation

categories.name: RateUnit
categories.description: Unit of measure in a rate expression.
categories.tooltip: Unit of measure in a rate expression

categories.name: Circumstance
categories.description: Macrolabel for labels pertaining to space and time; abstract/metaphoric locations such as states; and other categories that usually constitute semantically non-core properties of events.
categories.tooltip: Macrolabel for labels pertaining to space and time

categories.name: InsteadOf
categories.description: A default or already established thing for which something else stands in or is chosen as an alternative.
categories.tooltip: A default or already established thing for which something else stands in or is chosen as an alternative

categories.name: Participant
categories.description: Thing, usually an entity, that plays a causal role in an event.
categories.tooltip: Thing, usually an entity, that plays a causal role in an event

categories.name: Path
categories.description: The ground that must be covered in order for the motion to be complete.
categories.tooltip: The ground that must be covered in order for the motion to be complete.

categories.name: Means
categories.description: Secondary action or event that characterizes how the main event happens or is achieved.
categories.tooltip: Secondary action or event that characterizes how the main event happens or is achieved.

categories.name: Locus
categories.description: Location, condition, or value. May be abstract.
categories.tooltip: Location, condition, or value. May be abstract.

categories.name: `r
categories.description: Adverbial expression that does not count as a preposition or PP. E.g., "too" and "then" when spelled correctly (as opposed to "to", "than").
categories.tooltip: Adverbial expression that does not count as a preposition or PP

categories.name: `o
categories.description: Indefinite pronoun (tagged as a noun in PTB). (For historical reasons most pronouns are labeled ` -- `o was only recently introduced.)
categories.tooltip: Indefinite pronoun

categories.name: `j
categories.description: Adjectival expression.
categories.tooltip: Adjectival expression

categories.name: `i
categories.description: The word "to" used as infinitive marker, but not marking a Purpose or Function adjunct. Includes complements ("want to").
categories.tooltip: The word "to" used as infinitive marker, but not marking a Purpose or Function adjunct

categories.name: `d
categories.description: Discourse expression. Excludes subordinators marking a semantic role (such as time or explanation). For historical reasons some discourse expressions are labeled `.
categories.tooltip: Discourse expression

categories.name: `a
categories.description: Auxiliaries not POS-tagged as MD. Includes multiword "quasi-modals" like "have to" indicating necessity or obligation.
categories.tooltip: Auxiliaries not POS-tagged as MD. Includes multiword "quasi-modals" like "have to" indicating necessity or obligation

categories.description: ​Used for miscellaneous words that do not deserve supersenses, including "as" in as-as constructions, emoticons, and some other cases that were annotated before the label refinements below (`d, `o, etc.) were introduced.
categories.tooltip: ​Used for miscellaneous words that do not deserve supersenses
